<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be at rest • be resting</xh5><p> <i>be at rest—</i>1. be in a state of physical or mental repose: He sat in his chair, still, but not <u>at rest</u>: expectant evidently. 2. <i>(of an issue)</i> be settled or decided: I never can take any office under the present rulers; so that question <u>is at rest</u>. 3. <i>(euph.)</i> be dead and buried: He is now <u>at rest</u> after a full and dedicated life. We salute his extraordinary legacy...</p><p> <i>be resting—</i>1. <i>(euph., coll.)</i> be out of work: I am an interpreter.... At present I <u>am resting</u>. 2. <i>(of the body of a dead person)</i> remain at an undertaker’s, a chapel, etc. before burial: Remains will <u>be resting</u> at the John Doe Funeral Home.</p> </entry>
